{
  "name": "Printing As A Service",
  "annotation": {
    "text": "This example stream demonstrates how the fictional provider AlphaPrint meters Printing as a Service, billing customers by actual usage while also automating ink replenishment and printer maintenance.\n\nRaw printer events (pages printed, ink levels, health status) are collected, cleaned, and enriched with customer information, then split across three parallel paths: paper usage is aggregated for billing, low ink levels trigger reorder requests, and printers needing service are flagged for maintenance.\n\nAll external integrations are simulated with Log forwarders so you can run the stream out of the box, but the flow and logic mirror real-world use cases.",
    "color": "blue"
  },
